node.text:
My Dog Chases Everything! What Can I Do?

It is important to know how to use your tools the right way to get the outcome you want.

If you want to change the behavior ask your dog to go into a follower state rather than a leadership state. 

As Pack Leaders, we must be calm and confident.

Learn more @trainingcesarsway 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining

node.text:
In this episode, I deal with an aggressive dog, Duk Duk, that has bitten several people. 

Our relationships with are dogs are built on trust, respect, and love. I will try to gain Duk Duk's respect one step at a time. 

It is important as Pack Leaders to give direction to our dogs.

Full Video on YouTube!

Watch my new show Better Human, Better Dog on National Geographic Fridays 9/8c and on Disney+ with new episodes Every Wednesday! 

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.title: Can I Gain This Fearful Aggressive Dog’s Respect?

node.text:
In this first episode, I help Goliath, a pitbull, become a service dog to help his owner, John. This is the final challenge, where Goliath must find John.

Will Goliath pass my Final Test?

This episode is titled "Fit For Service."

My new show airs every Wednesday on @disneyplus and @natgeotv 9/8c every Friday!

Thank you all for your support!

#betterhumansbetterplanet #betterhumanbetterdog

node.text:
☀️

My New Show Better Human Better Dog premieres on @natgeotv & Disney+!

30 years ago I came to 🇺🇸 to become the best dog trainer in the world. I had a dream and that dream has transformed into a new mission.

A mission to make this world a better planet by bettering the way we as humans treat our animals through a natural, simple, and profound approach.

I am so excited for you all to see my new show. 

This is a video about me and my story. Get ready for #BetterHumanBetterDog

Blessings ❤️

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
Remember to allow the dog to come to you.

Stay calm and confident. Then claim your space.

The dog will then come to you and eventually relax in front of you. This is the time to give the dog affection.

A dog learns Nose, Eyes, and Ears.

It is important to practice No Touch, No Talk, No Eye Contact!

Cesar Millan: Better Human Better Dog premieres Friday at 9/8c on National Geographic. @natgeotv 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining #trainingtiptuesday

node.title: Training Tip Tuesday: How To Properly Greet A Dog! 🐕

node.text:
In my new YouTube Video, I visit the D'Amelio Pack! @dameliofamilyofficial 

I am so excited to partner with Halo and the D'Amelio family in creating a way to make sure our dogs are safe through our collar! @halocollar 

I showcase how to set rules, boundaries, and limitations.

We go through how to create calmness around food as well as the door.

As Pack Leaders we must take the leadership position with our dogs. 

One of the best ways to better our relationship with our dogs as well as be the authority figure is to take them on walks! 

Link in Bio to the Full Video!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
My Dog Chases Everything! What Can I Do?

It is important to know how to use your tools the right way to get the outcome you want.

If you want to change the behavior ask your dog to go into a follower state rather than a leadership state. 

As Pack Leaders, we must be calm and confident.

Learn more @trainingcesarsway 

#betterhumansbetterplanet #dogtraining

node.text:
These Dogs Attack Everyone! (Dog Nation Shorts)

In this episode, I help Sandie with her two dogs, Harley and Lola.

It is important to drain the pent up energy of our dogs to prevent any unwanted behaviors.

Dogs are mirrors of who we are and the environment we create!

Can I help Sandie solve her problems?

Full Video on Youtube!

#betterhumansbetterplanet

Better Human Better Dog Mini Moment 🐕

It is important to reward our dogs at the right time!

Remember we must keep it simple and profound. 

Watch the new episode 9/8c on @natgeotv every Friday! And on @disneyplus every Wednesday!

#betterhumanbetterdog

node.text:
#nationaldogday 

Today we celebrate our best friends, our dogs! 🐕

Thank you for showing us what it means to be loved unconditionally. 

Our relationships are built on trust, respect, and love. 

Life is simple, we make it complicated and our dogs teach us how to live in the moment. 

Let’s celebrate by going on an amazing pack walk today!

We love you ❤️

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
In this episode, I deal with an aggressive dog, Duk Duk, that has bitten several people. 

Our relationships with are dogs are built on trust, respect, and love. I will try to gain Duk Duk's respect one step at a time. 

It is important as Pack Leaders to give direction to our dogs.

Full Video on YouTube!

Watch my new show Better Human, Better Dog on National Geographic Fridays 9/8c and on Disney+ with new episodes Every Wednesday! 

#betterhumansbetterplanet

node.text:
In this Better Human Better Dog episode, I help Millie, a 7 month Doxon who has a bad habit from eating trash off the ground.

Can Millie's owner, Brittany, lead Millie through this final test?

It is important to start in calmness before entering a situation. 

Always control the nose, if you guide the nose the dog will follow!

My new show airs every Friday at 9/8c on @natgeotv and Every Wednesday on @disneyplus 

Full Exercise on Youtube!

#betterhumanbetterdog

node.text:
How To Socialize Other Dogs!

Follow, Play, Explore

At the dog park, dogs practice play and explore.

A great way to prepare for the dog park is to take your dog on a walk before you go!

We must be aware of the energy of our dogs before we bring them to the dog park!

Watch my new show Better Human Better Dog on @natgeotv and @disneyplus 

#betterhumanbetterdog #dogtraining

Pack Profile Friday!
